Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop onto a large #baking tray{} in a single layer (use 2 trays if you need to - as you'll be adding the veggies to the tray later!). Drizzle with @olive oil{} and sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Toss to coat in the oil, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{15%minutes}.

In the meantime, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into roughly 3cm pieces. Trim the @courgette{1} then halve lengthways. Cut widthways into 2cm wide slices. Halve and peel the @red onion{1}. Slice each half into four wedges. Peel and thinly slice the @garlic clove{1}. Drain the @halloumi{250%g} and slice widthways into three pieces per person.

When the potatoes have been roasting for 15 mins, add the veggies and garlic slices to the #tray{} and pour over another drizzle of oil and some more salt and pepper. Give everything a good toss, then return to the oven for another ~{15%minutes}.

After 15 minutes when the veggies are starting to soften and colour, give everything another toss and lay the halloumi slices on top. Return to the oven for a final ~{15-20%minutes}. By this point, the halloumi should be nicely golden round the edges and the veggies nicely roasted.

While the halloumi is in the oven, pop the @green pesto{45%g} into a #small bowl{} and add the @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Mix it together - it should be drizzling consistency. Now, do some washing up and get ready to serve!

Once the veggies and the halloumi are nicely coloured, share between your plates (keeping the halloumi on top for nice presentation!). Spoon the pesto drizzle all over. Dig in!

> Minimal washing up, quick to prep, and packed with fresh summery flavours, this recipe is perfect for feeding a crowd.